{"id":"wax","term":"Wax","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Made by melting the combs of bees. Mentioned (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 22:14\">Ps. 22:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 68:2\">68:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 97:5\">97:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Micah 1:4\">Micah 1:4</a>) in illustration.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Psalms 22:14","Psalms 68:2","Psalms 97:5","Micah 1:4"]}